# BX-09 Sprint — Comprehensive Cross-Story Analysis

**Date:** April 15, 2026

All four stories are **buyer-side checkout** features that share the same screen (`CheckoutScreen.tsx`) and the same data flow. They must be implemented together to fully pass each other's acceptance criteria.

---

## Story Dependency Map

```
BX-09-004 (Address Validation)     ← FOUNDATION — we built this
    ↓ provides valid address + GPS coords to
BX-09-001 (Shipping Fee Per Seller) ← needs address for zone detection
    ↓ provides per-seller shipping fee to
BX-09-002 (Choose Shipping Method)  ← needs fee engine + method list
    ↓ provides selected method to
BX-09-003 (Show Estimated Delivery) ← needs method for ETA calculation
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **BX-09-004 is the foundation layer. The other three stories cannot fully work without it.** Our work on BX-09-004 gave them the validated address + GPS coordinates they need. The BX-09-004 gaps have now been closed as of April 15 — the only remaining item (#9 recalculation) is intentionally deferred to BX-09-001 where the real shipping engine will be built.

---

## Current Shipping Logic (Before BX-09-001/002/003)

```typescript
// CheckoutScreen.tsx line 424 — THIS IS ALL THERE IS:
fees[seller] = storeSubtotal >= 500 ? 0 : 50;
```

- **Hardcoded** ₱50 flat fee per seller, free if subtotal ≥ ₱500
- **No courier integration** — no zone detection, no weight calculation
- **No method selection** — no picker, no options
- **No ETA** — no delivery estimate shown anywhere
- **No recalculation** on address change — fee is purely subtotal-based
- **No `shipping_zones` or `shipping_config` table usage**

---

## Full Acceptance Criteria Scorecard

### Legend
- ✅ **Pass** — fully implemented by our BX-09-004 work
- 🟡 **Partial** — partially covered, needs completion
- ❌ **Not Started** — not implemented yet
- 🔗 **Depends on other story** — will be solved when that story is built

